
Ranger Help for: carve bow
==========================

SYNTAX:      carve <shortbow/crossbow/longbow>
USAGE:       forest,jungle,swamp
SLOT COST:   10
BASE SP:     60 sp
SKILL TYPE:  bow

SUMMARY:    
This skill allows a Ranger to carve one of three types of bows from
wooded areas. The three bows are shortbow, longbow and crossbow. Each
has its advantages and disadvantages as well as more advanced special
attacks for each. The shortbow, loads faster, but hits with less power.
The longbow hits pretty hard, but takes longer to load. Both the shortbow
and longbow use arrows. The crossbow hits the hardest, and takes the
longest to load. Crossbows use bolts to fire. As a Ranger's level goes up,
so does his or her ability to carve a bow. The quality of a bow affects
how well a Ranger shoots it, as well as how tough it is in hand to hand
combat. When used in hand to hand combat, a bow becomes something more
akin to a staff, so it is weapon spec'ed as a medium blunt weapon. Ammo
for the bows can be carved from wooded areas as well, provided the Ranger
knows the skill carve arrow. Once arrows and bolts have been carved, they
can be enhanced with several other Ranger skills.

Once a bow has been carved. You need to specify where you want to load ammo
from by typing 'load from <container>' where container can be the name of
a container you have, such as your quiver, or from 'me', which loads arrows
from the arrows you are holding in your hands. The best arrows or bolts you
have are automatically used first and you can change from what container
you wish to load from at any time. Too fire your bow at someone, type
'fire <target>' and you will either score a hit or miss. Arrows and bolts
can be reused if you get them back by slaying your opponent or picking up
arrows or bolts that you shot and missed with. 

